DOCUMENT();

loadMacros(
	"PGstandard.pl",	# Standard macros for PG language
	"MathObjects.pl",
	"PGML.pl",
	"parserPopUp.pl",
	"parserMultiAnswer.pl",
	"weightedGrader.pl",
	"source.pl",			# allows code to be displayed on certain sites
	"PGcourse.pl", 	 # Customization file for the course
);

#######################################################
#Setup

TEXT(beginproblem());

$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

Context("Numeric");		# or Complex

#---------------Tolerance------------------#
Context()->flags->set(
tolerance=>.02,
tolType=>'relative');  #relative or absolute

#-------------- Image Scaling---------------#
$imgScale =0.2;

$height = $imgScale*2310;

$width = $imgScale*2418;
		#aspect ratio


#---- Random variables for this problem --------#
$massA = random(1,2,0.1);
$vel = random(2,3,0.1);
$massB = $massA/2;
$length = random(1,2,0.1);

#---- Formulas to compute answers --------------#
$radA = $length;
$radB = $length/2;
$angVel = $radA*$massA*$vel/($radA**2*$massA+$radB**2*$massB);
$velA2 = $angVel*$radA;

#---- Answers to the problem -----------------------#
$ansA = abs($velA2);

########################################################;
#PGML

BEGIN_PGML	

[@ image( "20-P-MOM-DY-29.png", width=>[$width], height=>[$height]) @]*

A [`m_A = [$massA] kg`] block is attached to the end of a [`l = [$length] m`] rigid rod with negligible mass. 
The other end of the rod is  connected to a pivot which allows the rod to rotate in the horizontal plane.  
If the mass is traveling at the velocity [`v_A = [$vel] m/s`] before the rod has a completely inelastic collision 
with a [`m_B = [$massB] kg`] mass at the middle of the rod, determine the magnitude of the velocity of block [`A`]
after the collision.


[`|v| =`] [____]{"$ansA"} [`m/s`]

END_PGML

BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION

